text.tspan: What we did: simulating the night sky
In general nxn gaussian distributions of brightness.
Here all are 3x3 kernels (red and yellow)
Generator that creates star like objects and changes:
* speed as in pixels per seconds
* as single satellite or starlink train of m satellites on some track
* time of entering into the frame
For each frame, the nxn satellite is moved to its position.
Depending on the speed this can result in "jumps".
The "integration time" of the camera is modeled.
Each frame has subframes where kernel is moved ...
Also, each nxn kernel can be scalled up for better anti-aliasing.
This is the end.....result for now
... and then combined to the final frame.
